HEADWORD: Prudentialist
<hw>Pru*den"tial*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is governed by, or
acts from, prudential motives.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
